Both message tools fail. The issue is that this isolated cron session doesn't have a user authorization context. The delivery previews showed the announce goes to feishu:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 which is the tts account's own open_id.

Looking at the cron job's delivery configuration:
```
"deliveryPreviews": {
  "91574622-694d-4f41-88f2-46d18beb130d": {
    "label": "announce -> feishu:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68",
    "detail": "explicit"
  }
}
```

The announce delivery is going to ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 (the tts bot itself), not to HALEI. The cron job's delivery configuration needs to be updated to send to HALEI's open_id instead.

However, I got an error when trying to update the cron job ("Cron tool is restricted to the current cron job"). Let me try to send a message to myself (the tts account) as a workaround, and note that the cron delivery target needs fixing.

Actually, I should just give up on sending the message and report what happened. The cron session doesn't have proper message-sending authority to HALEI. The daily has been written. Let me just summarize the results.
